Pytest Playwright Locators Guide

What is a Locator?
A locator is how Playwright finds elements on a webpage.

Common Playwright Locators:

1. By Text
page.locator("text=Forgot Password?").click()

2. By ID
page.locator("#username").fill("vinod")
page.locator("#password").fill("1234")

3. By Name
page.locator("[name='username']").fill("vinod")

4. By CSS Selector
page.locator("input[type='text']").fill("vinod")

5. By XPath (Avoid if possible)
page.locator("//input[@id='username']").fill("vinod")

6. By Role (Recommended)
page.get_by_role("button", name="Login").click()
page.get_by_role("link", name="Forgot Password?").click()

7. By Label (Best for forms)
page.get_by_label("Username").fill("vinod")
page.get_by_label("Password").fill("1234")

8. By Placeholder
page.get_by_placeholder("Username").fill("vinod")

Example Test:

def test_login(page):
    page.goto("your_url")
    page.get_by_label("Username").fill("vinod")
    page.get_by_label("Password").fill("1234")
    page.get_by_role("button", name="Login").click()

Best Practices:
- Prefer get_by_role and get_by_label
- Use ID when available
- Avoid XPath and index-based locators

